ld not process queue.','Queue processed, reloading page.'=>'Queue processed, reloading page.','Defer jQuery and other non-aggregated JS-files? (deprecated)'=>'Defer jQuery and other non-aggregated JS-files? (deprecated)','Inline critical CSS?'=>'Inline critical CSS?','Optimize CSS?'=>'Optimise CSS?','Optimize JS?'=>'Optimise JS?','Optimize this page?'=>'Optimise this page?','Autoptimize this page'=>'Autoptimize this page','Automatically serve AVIF image format to any browser that supports it.'=>'Automatically serve AVIF image format to any browser that supports it.','Enable configuration per post/ page?'=>'Enable configuration per post/ page?','Eliminate render-blocking CSS?'=>'Eliminate render-blocking CSS?','Autoptimize combines your theme & plugins\' JavaScript, but does not know what is used and what not. If Google Pagespeed Insights detects unused JavaScript, consider using a plugin like "Plugin Organizer" or similar to manage what JavaScript is added where.'=>'Autoptimize combines your theme and plugins\' JavaScript, but does not know what is used and what is not. If Google Pagespeed Insights detects unused JavaScript, consider using a plugin like "Plugin Organizer" or similar to manage what JavaScript is added and where.','A comma-separated list of scripts you do not want optimized, for example \'whatever.js, my_var\' (without the quotes).'=>'A comma-separated list of scripts you do not want optimised, for example \'whatever.js, my_var\' (without the quotes).','Also defer inline JS?'=>'Also defer inline JS?','Let Autoptimize also extract JS from the HTML (discouraged as it can make Autoptimize\'s cache size grow quickly)'=>'Let Autoptimize also extract JS from the HTML (discouraged as it can make Autoptimize\'s cache size grow quickly)','you can click %1$shere to refresh your quota status%2$s'=>'you can click %1$shere to refresh your quota status%2$s','Lazy-load from nth image'=>'Lazy-load from nth image','Comma-separated list of image classes or filenames that should not be optimized.'=>'Comma-separated list of image classes or filenames that should not be optimised.','Optimization exclusions'=>'Optimisation exclusions','Do not aggregate but defer?'=>'Do not aggregate but defer?','Queue processing time limit'=>'Queue processing time limit','If you have enough CDN quota remaining, then you may need to %1$sassociate your domain%2$s to your Shortpixel account.'=>'If you have enough CDN quota remaining, then you may need to %1$sassociate your domain%2$s to your Shortpixel account.','Unload critical CSS after page load?'=>'Unload critical CSS after page load?','In rare cases the critical CSS needs to be removed once the full CSS loads, this option makes it so!'=>'In rare cases, the critical CSS needs to be removed once the full CSS loads – this option makes it so!','Enable 404 fallbacks?'=>'Enable 404 fallbacks?','Something went wrong when checking your API key, make sure you server can communicate with https://criticalcss.com and/ or try again later.'=>'Something went wrong when checking your API key, make sure you server can communicate with https://criticalcss.com and/ or try again later.','Invalid'=>'Invalid','Valid'=>'Valid','Inlining all CSS is an easy way to stop the CSS from being render-blocking, but is generally not recommended because the size of the HTML increases significantly. Additionally it might push meta-tags down to a position where e.g. Facebook and Whatsapp will not find them any more, breaking thumbnails when sharing.'=>'Inlining all CSS is an easy way to stop the CSS from being render-blocking, but is generally not recommended because the size of the HTML increases significantly. Additionally it might push meta-tags down to a position where e.g. Facebook and WhatsApp will not find them any more, breaking thumbnails when sharing.','Sometimes Autoptimized JS/ CSS is referenced in cached HTML but is already removed, resulting in broken sites. With this option on, Autoptimize will try to redirect those not-found files to "fallback"-versions, keeping the page/ site somewhat intact. In some cases this will require extra web-server level configuration to ensure %1$swp-content/autoptimize_404_handler.php%2$s is set to handle 404\'s in %1$swp-content/cache/autoptimize%2$s.'=>'Sometimes Autoptimized JS/ CSS is referenced in cached HTML but is already removed, resulting in broken sites. With this option on, Autoptimize will try to redirect those not-found files to "fallback" versions, keeping the page/site somewhat intact. In some cases this will require extra web-server level configuration to ensure %1$swp-content/autoptimize_404_handler.php%2$s is set to handle 404\'s in %1$swp-content/cache/autoptimize%2$s.','Remove all rules'=>'Remove all rules','At any time you can delete an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> or <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule by cliking on "Remove" button of the desired rule and saving your changes.'=>'At any time you can delete an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> or <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule by cliking on "Remove" button of the desired rule and saving your changes.','Add CSS To All Rules'=>'Add CSS to all rules','Edit Default Rule CSS'=>'Edit default rule CSS','Add New Rule'=>'Add new rule','You can create <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rules for specific page paths (URL). Longer, more specific paths have higher priority over shorter ones, which in turn have higher priority over <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rules. Also, critical CSS files from <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> <strong>rules are NEVER updated automatically.</strong>'=>'You can create <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rules for specific page paths (URL). Longer, more specific paths have higher priority over shorter ones, which in turn have higher priority over <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rules. Also, critical CSS files from <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> <strong>rules are NEVER updated automatically.</strong>','If you want to make any fine tunning in the critical CSS file of an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule, click on "Edit" button of that rule, change what you need, submit and save it. The rule you\'ve just edited becomes a <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule then.'=>'If you want to make any fine tuning in the critical CSS file of an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule, click on "Edit" button of that rule, change what you need, submit and save it. The rule you\'ve just edited becomes a <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule then.','These requests also creates an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule for you. The critical CSS files from <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> <strong>rules are updated automatically</strong> when a CSS file in your theme or frontend plugins changes.'=>'These requests also creates an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule for you. The critical CSS files from <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> <strong>rules are updated automatically</strong> when a CSS file in your theme or front end plugins changes.','Upon a request to any of the frontend pages made by a <strong>not logged in user</strong>, it will <strong>asynchronously</strong> fetch and update the critical CSS from <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for conditional tags you have on your site (e.g. is_page, is_single, is_archive etc.)'=>'Upon a request to any of the front end pages made by a <strong>not logged in user</strong>, it will <strong>asynchronously</strong> fetch and update the critical CSS from <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for conditional tags you have on your site (e.g. is_page, is_single, is_archive etc.)','<strong>CAUTION! Only use debug mode on production/live environments for ad-hoc troubleshooting and remember to turn it back off after</strong>, as this generates a lot of log-data.<br />Check the box above to enable Autoptimize 