l','Remove'=>'Remove','Edit'=>'Edit','AUTO'=>'AUTO','MANUAL'=>'MANUAL','To be fetched from criticalcss.com in the next queue run...'=>'To be fetched from criticalcss.com in the next queue run...','Critical CSS File'=>'Critical CSS File','Target'=>'Target','Type'=>'Type','Conditional Tags, Custom Post Types and Page Templates Rules'=>'Conditional Tags, Custom Post Types and Page Templates Rules','Path Based Rules'=>'Path Based Rules','Paste your minified default critical CSS here and hit submit to save. This is the critical CSS to be used for every page not matching any rule.'=>'Paste your minified default critical CSS here and hit submit to save. This is the critical CSS to be used for every page not matching any rule.','When a valid <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> API key is in place, Autoptimize starts to operate <strong>automatically</strong>.'=>'When a valid <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> API key is in place, Autoptimize starts to operate <strong>automatically</strong>.','In some (rare) cases the generation of critical CSS works better with the original CSS instead of the Autoptimized one, this option enables that behavior.'=>'In some (rare) cases the generation of critical CSS works better with the original CSS instead of the Autoptimized one, this option enables that behaviour.','<a href="https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> default viewport size is 1400x1080 pixels (width x height). You can change this size by typing a desired width and height values above. Allowed value ranges are from 800 to 4096 for width and from 600 to 2160 for height.'=>'<a href="https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> default viewport size is 1400x1080 pixels (width x height). You can change this size by typing a desired width and height values above. Allowed value ranges are from 800 to 4096 for width and from 600 to 2160 for height.','Debug Mode'=>'Debug Mode','Only requests from this domain will be sent for Critical CSS generation (pricing is per domain/ month).'=>'Only requests from this domain will be sent for Critical CSS generation (pricing is per domain/ month).','Don\'t leave this empty, put e.g. https://example.net/ or simply \'none\' to disable domain binding.'=>'Don\'t leave this empty, put e.g. https://example.net/ or simply \'none\' to disable domain binding.','Bound domain'=>'Bound domain','Defer all non-aggregated JS, including jQuery and inline JS to fix remaining render-blocking issues. Make sure to test your site thoroughly when activating this option!'=>'Defer all non-aggregated JS, including jQuery and inline JS to fix remaining render-blocking issues. Make sure to test your site thoroughly when activating this option!','By default for each page a separate rule is generated. If your pages have (semi-)identical above the fold look and feel and you want to keep the rules lean, you can disable that so one rule is created to all pages.'=>'By default for each page a separate rule is generated. If your pages have (semi-)identical above the fold look and feel and you want to keep the rules lean, you can disable that so one rule is created to all pages.','Force path-based rules to be generated for pages?'=>'Force path-based rules to be generated for pages?','Add CCSS for logged in users?'=>'Add CCSS for logged in users?','Fetch Original CSS'=>'Fetch Original CSS','.button-special,//#footer'=>'.button-special,//#footer','Force Include CSS selectors'=>'Force Include CSS selectors','Force include CSS selectors can be used to style dynamic content that is not part of the HTML that is seen during the Critical CSS generation. To use this feature, add comma separated values with both simple strings and/or regular expressions to match the desired selectors. Regular expressions must be preceeded by two forward slashes. For instance: <code>.button-special,//#footer</code>. In this example <code>.button-special</code> will match <code>.button-special</code> selector only, while <code>//#footer</code> will match <code>#footer</code>, <code>#footer-address</code> and <code>#footer-phone</code> selectors in case they exist.<br />Do take into account that changing this setting will only affect new/ updated rules, so you might want to remove old rules and clear your page cache to expedite the forceIncludes becoming used.'=>'Force include CSS selectors can be used to style dynamic content that is not part of the HTML that is seen during the Critical CSS generation. To use this feature, add comma separated values with both simple strings and/or regular expressions to match the desired selectors. Regular expressions must be preceeded by two forward slashes. For instance: <code>.button-special,//#footer</code>. In this example <code>.button-special</code> will match <code>.button-special</code> selector only, while <code>//#footer</code> will match <code>#footer</code>, <code>#footer-address</code> and <code>#footer-phone</code> selectors in case they exist.<br />Do take into account that changing this setting will only affect new/ updated rules, so you might want to remove old rules and clear your page cache to expedite the forceIncludes becoming used.','Critical CSS is generated by criticalcss.com from your pages as seen by an "anonymous visitor". Disable this option if you don\'t want the "visitor" critical CSS to be used for logged in users.'=>'Critical CSS is generated by criticalcss.com from your pages as seen by an "anonymous visitor". Disable this option if you don\'t want the "visitor" critical CSS to be used for logged in users.','Viewport Size'=>'Viewport Size','None'=>'None','Height'=>'Height','Width'=>'Width','Advanced Settings'=>'Advanced Settings','Retry'=>'Retry','Delete all jobs?'=>'Delete all jobs?','Cancel'=>'Cancel','Delete'=>'Delete','Job status is '=>'Job status is ','N/A'=>'N/A','UNKNOWN'=>'UNKNOWN','Get Help'=>'Get Help','ERROR'=>'ERROR','DONE'=>'DONE','- Validation: '=>'- Validation: ','- Result: '=>'- Result: ','- Status: '=>'- Status: ','- Job ID: '=>'- Job ID: ','Info from criticalcss.com:'=>'Info from criticalcss.com:','REVIEW'=>'REVIEW','PENDING'=>'PENDING','New'=>'New','Remove all jobs'=>'Remove all jobs','Actions'=>'Actions','Finish Date'=>'Finish Date','Creation Date'=>'Creation Date','Page Type'=>'Page Type','Page Path'=>'Page Path','Target Rule'=>'Target Rule','Status'=>'Status','Sometimes an unknown condition can happen. In this case, the job status becomes <span class="badge unknown">U</span> and you may want to ask <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for help or just delete it.'=>'Sometimes an unknown condition can happen. In this case, the job status becomes <span class="badge unknown">U</span> and you may want to ask <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for help or just delete it.','To get more information about jobs statuses, specially the ones with <span class="badge error">E</span> and <span class="badge unknown">U</span> status, hover your mouse in the status badge of that job. This information might be crucial when contacting <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for assistance.'=>'To get more information about jobs statuses, specially the ones with <span class="badge error">E</span> and <span class="badge unknown">U</span> status, hover your mouse in the status badge of that job. This information might be crucial when contacting <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for assistance.','When things go wrong, a job is marked as <span class="badge error">E</span>. You can retry faulty jobs, delete them or get in touch with <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for assistance.'=>'When things go wrong, a job is marked as <span class="badge error">E</span>. You can retry faulty jobs, delete them or get in touch with <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for assistance.','As soon as <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> returns a valid critical CSS file, the job is then finished and removed from the queue.'=>'As soon as <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> returns a valid critical CSS file, the job is then finished and removed from the queue.','When the conditions to create a job are met (i.e. user not logged in, no matching <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule or CSS files has changed for an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule), a <span class="badge new">N</span> job is created in the queue.'=>'When the conditions to create a job are met (i.e. user not logged in, no matching <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule or CSS files has changed for an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule), a <span class="badge new">N</span> job is created in the queue.','The queue operates <strong>automatically, asynchronously and on regular intervals of 10 minutes.</strong> To view updated queue status, refresh this page.'=>'The queue operates <strong>automatically, asynchronously and on regular intervals of 10 minutes.</strong> To view updated queue status, refresh this page.','TL;DR:<br /><strong>Queue runs every 10 minutes.</strong> Job statuses are <span class="badge new">N</span> for NEW, <span class="badge pending">P</span> for PENDING, <span class="badge error">E</span> for ERROR and <span class="badge unknown">U</span> for UNKOWN.'=>'TL;DR:<br /><strong>Queue runs every 10 minutes.</strong> Job statuses are <span class="badge new">N</span> for NEW, <span class="badge pending">P</span> for PENDING, <span class="badge error">E</span> for ERROR and <span class="badge unknown">U</span> for UNKOWN.','Import Settings'=>'Import Settings','Export Settings'=>'Export Settings','<p>Critical CSS settings canno